{
  "keyword": "DLTOBJ",
  "description": "Delete Object (DLTOBJ)",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "OBJ",
      "description": "Object",
      "help": "Object (OBJ)\n\nSpecifies the objects which you want to delete and the library or libraries from which the objects are to be deleted.\n\nThis is a required parameter.\n\nQualifier 1: Object\n\nNote: System library names such as library QSYS are allowed, but be very careful about specifying a system library name with an object name of *ALL.\n\nQualifier 2: Library\n\nUser libraries are all libraries with names that do not begin with the letter Q except for the following:\n\nAlthough the following libraries with names that begin with the letter Q are provided by IBM, they typically contain user data that changes frequently. Therefore, these libraries are also considered user libraries:",
      "inputType": "group",
      "required": true,
      "groupKind": "qualified",
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "LIB",
          "description": "Library",
          "help": "指定できる特殊値: *LIBL, *CURLIB, *USRLIBL, *ALL, *ALLUSR",
          "inputType": "text",
          "required": false,
          "defaultValue": "*LIBL",
          "attributes": {
            "characterSet": "upper",
            "maxLength": 10
          },
          "placeholder": "*LIBL"
        },
        {
          "name": "OBJ",
          "description": "Object",
          "help": "指定できる特殊値: *ALL",
          "inputType": "text",
          "required": true,
          "attributes": {
            "characterSet": "upper",
            "maxLength": 10
          },
          "placeholder": "OBJ"
        }
      ],
      "positional": 1,
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "OBJTYPE",
      "description": "Object type",
      "help": "Object type (OBJTYPE)\n\nSpecifies the type of object which you want to delete.\n\nTo see a complete list of object types when prompting this command, position the cursor on the field for this parameter and press F4 (Prompt). For a description of the object types, see \"Object types\" in the CL topic collection in the Programming category in the IBM i Information Center at http://www.ibm.com/systems/i/infocenter/.\n\nThis is a required parameter.",
