    {
      "name": "ASPDEV",
      "description": "ASP device",
      "help": "ASP device (ASPDEV)\n\nSpecifies the auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name where storage is allocated for the library containing the object. If the library resides in an ASP that is not part of the thread's library name space, this parameter must be specified to ensure the correct library is searched. If this parameter is used when the library qualifier specified for the Object (OBJ) parameter is *CURLIB, *LIBL, or *USRLIBL, ASPDEV(*) is the only valid value.\n\nSpecify the name of the primary or secondary ASP device to be searched. The primary or secondary ASP must have been activated (by varying on the ASP device) and have a status of 'Available'. The system ASP (ASP 1) and defined basic user ASPs (ASPs 2-32) will not be searched.\n\nNote: To specify a specific auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name, you must have use (*USE) authority for each ASP device in the ASP group.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *, *ALLAVL, *CURASPGRP, *SYSBAS",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "placeholder": "*",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "RMVMSG",
      "description": "Remove message",
      "help": "Remove message (RMVMSG)\n\nSpecifies whether or not to remove completion and informational messages related to the deletion of objects from the job log. Messages are only removed if the object was successfully deleted. Diagnostic and escape messages are not removed for objects that could not be deleted.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*NO",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "restricted": true
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*NO",
          "value": "*NO"
        },
        {
          "label": "*YES",
          "value": "*YES"
        }
      ],
      "basic": true
    }
  ],
  "examples": [
    {
      "code": "DLTOBJ OBJ(MYLIB/*ALL) OBJTYPE(*USRSPC) ASPDEV(*) RMVMSG(*NO)"
    },
    {
      "code": "DLTOBJ OBJ(QSYS/TESTLIBXY*) OBJTYPE(*LIB) ASPDEV(*ALLAVL)"
    }
  ],
